  <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
    <subfield code="o">30</subfield>
    <subfield code="m">It is worth emphasizing the fact that, for spinning Kerr-Newman black holes, the ordinary differential equations which determine the angular and radial behaviors of the charged massive scalar fields [see Eqs. (10) and (12), respectively] are coupled by the angular eigenvalues {Klm}</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
    <subfield code="o">31</subfield>
    <subfield code="m">For brevity, we shall henceforth omit the harmonic indices {l, m} of the scalar field mode</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
    <subfield code="o">32</subfield>
